==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Serbonian
<hw>Ser*bo"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Relating to the
lake of Serbonis in Egypt, which by reason of the sand blowing into it
had a deceptive appearance of being solid land, but was a bog.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A gulf profound as that <qex>Serbonian</qex> bog . . . ⟦br⟧
Where armies whole have sunk.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sere</ent>⟦br⟧
